The paper deals with deep learning applied to image analysis, specifically in the medical domain. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of unlabelled data to address the issue of small labelled datasets suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with interpretability, which is a key issue in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses optimization techniques, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
